"n.朴素，艰苦 【英】 n.朴素，艰苦(tight economy) 【考】 反义词：ostentation (炫耀) n. 节俭(严格节约, 经济紧缩); 简朴; 艰苦 【例】wartime austerity 战时节俭 【记】au读: 诶哟, sterity = sterility(n 不毛之地)－需要节俭 【反】ostentation(n 卖弄, 摆阔) 【记】sterile 贫脊的 austerity (n.)  mid-14c., ""sternness, harshness,"" from Old French austerite ""harshness, cruelty"" (14c.) and directly from Late Latin austeritatem (nominative austeritas), from austerus (see austere). Of severe self-discipline, from 1580s; hence ""severe simplicity"" (1875); applied during World War II to national policies limiting non-essentials as a wartime economy."
